AGI - A challenging manoeuvre to disengage a Flixbus, without passengers on board, is underway tonight at 4 in Val Fresca, Comasco. Firefighters are looking in every way to 'freeze' working, report, "in complex and risky conditions for the possible transfer of the road > during recovery operations".
The driver, who then descended without bringing back damage, would have misguided. To facilitate disconnection operations, it was necessary to remove some plants along the road and to deactivate the electrical cables by the staff of Enel. The maneuvers are expected to continue for several hours.
Due to the accident, the road is currently closed to traffic. The vigilants also report damage to containment walls and fences near the site of the accident. Local Police are on site to ensure security and manage traffic.&nbsp;
